    <h2>The Importance of Hydration</h2>
    <div class="image-container">
      <img src="images/hydration.jpg" alt="Hydration" />
    </div>
    <p>
      Staying hydrated is crucial for maintaining overall health. Water is
      essential for various bodily functions, including:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Regulating body temperature</li>
      <li>Maintaining electrolyte balance</li>
      <li>Supporting digestion and nutrient absorption</li>
      <li>Removing waste products from the body</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>The Role of Fiber</h2>
    <div class="image-container">
      <img src="images/fiber_foods.jpg" alt="Fiber Foods" />
    </div>
    <p>Fiber is an important component of a healthy diet. It helps to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Promote healthy digestion</li>
      <li>Prevent constipation</li>
      <li>Maintain healthy blood sugar levels</li>
      <li>Lower cholesterol levels</li>
      <li>Support weight management</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Good sources of fiber include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Fruits: Apples, bananas, oranges, berries</li>
      <li>Vegetables: Carrots, broccoli, spinach, peas</li>
      <li>Whole grains: Oats, brown rice, whole wheat bread</li>
      <li>Legumes: Beans, lentils, chickpeas</li>
      <li>Nuts and seeds: Almonds, chia seeds, flaxseeds</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Malnutrition Diseases and Their Effects</h2>
    <table>
      <tr>
        <th>Disease</th>
        <th>Cause</th>
        <th>Symptoms</th>
        <th>Prevention</th>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Kwashiorkor</td>
        <td>Severe protein deficiency</td>
        <td>Swelling, enlarged liver, skin conditions</td>
        <td>
          Ensure adequate protein intake from sources like meat, eggs, and
          legumes.
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Marasmus</td>
        <td>Severe calorie deficiency</td>
        <td>Severe weight loss, muscle wasting, fatigue</td>
        <td>
          Consume sufficient calories from a balanced diet including
          carbohydrates, proteins, and fats.
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Rickets</td>
        <td>Vitamin D deficiency</td>
        <td>Weak or soft bones, stunted growth, skeletal deformities</td>
        <td>
          Get adequate sunlight exposure and consume vitamin D-rich foods like
          fish and fortified dairy products.
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Scurvy</td>
        <td>Vitamin C deficiency</td>
        <td>Bleeding gums, weakness, bruising</td>
        <td>
          Include vitamin C-rich foods like citrus fruits, tomatoes, and bell
          peppers in your diet.
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Anemia</td>
        <td>Iron deficiency</td>
        <td>Fatigue, weakness, pale skin</td>
        <td>
          Consume iron-rich foods like red meat, beans, and spinach, and
          consider iron supplements if necessary.
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table>
    <p>
      It is important to maintain a balanced diet to prevent these diseases
      and ensure overall health and well-being.
    </p>
    <h2>How to Cook Good Food with Better Nutrition</h2>
    <div class="image-container">
      <img src="images/cooking.jpg" alt="Cooking" />
    </div>
    <p>
      Cooking nutritious meals is essential for maintaining a healthy
      lifestyle. Here are some tips on how to cook good food with better
      nutrition:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Use Fresh Ingredients:</strong> Fresh fruits, vegetables, and
        lean meats are more nutritious than processed foods.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Minimize Use of Salt and Sugar:</strong> Excessive salt and
        sugar can lead to health issues. Use herbs and spices for flavor
        instead.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Choose Healthy Cooking Methods:</strong> Opt for grilling,
        steaming, baking, or saut√©ing instead of frying.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Include a Variety of Foods:</strong> Ensure your meals include
        a balance of carbohydrates, proteins, fats, vitamins, and minerals.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Control Portion Sizes:</strong> Eating the right amount of
        food helps maintain a healthy weight and prevents overeating.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Stay Hydrated:</strong> Drink plenty of water throughout the
        day and include hydrating foods like fruits and vegetables in your
        diet.
      </li>
    </ul>
